A vintage-style illustration of a well-worn leather travel suitcase sitting open on an airport terminal floor at dawn, with a boarding pass and passport tucked into the front pocket. Through massive windows behind it, a classic Boeing 747 is visible on the tarmac, silhouetted against a soft pink and orange sunrise sky. The scene has the warm, slightly faded color palette of 1960s travel posters, with gentle grain texture and muted tones suggesting adventure and anticipation. A crumpled airline blanket and empty coffee cup rest beside the suitcase, hinting at a long journey ahead.
